-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INTRODUCTION: 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    APM is all about monitoring the application performance.
    New Relic is APM (Application Performance Monitoring) which is Software as a Service.  
    New Relic has multiple integrations like slack etc. 

    It helps to check,
        Response time of servers. 
        Alert on time. 
        To check any errors. 
        Stack trace (UI -> Service -> DB)

    It helps business by,
        Reduce outages.
        View customer experience. 
        Meet SLA. 
        Reduce MTTR (Mean Time To Recovery)


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ARCHITECTURE:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    
    Browser Monitoring, Application (Node JS, Java etc), Infra, Database, Mobiles => New relic => Slack, Pagerduty etc. 

    It works by Agent. Depends upon language, agent will be changed. 
    Agent is light weight.
    It collects lot of metrics like user behaviour etc. 


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INSTALLATION: 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    1. Signup the account (https://newrelic.com/signup)
    2. Select the operating system. 
    3. New relic installation will be shared and run the installation in machine. 
    4. Once installation is completed, dashboard will be shared.


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- APPLICATION SETUP for APM (Node JS)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    New Relic -> APM -> Select App (or) Service -> Node.js -> Installation procedure available.

        1. Select application name
        2. Install the agent. 
        3. Download custom configuration file and place under root directory of project. 
        4. Add code to application main module in starting (require('newrelic');)
        5. Start the aplpication.
        6. Connect with logs and infrastructure using commands shared. 


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
AWS Integrations: 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/infrastructure/amazon-integrations/connect/connect-aws-new-relic-infrastructure-monitoring/


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
APPLICATION SETUP for APM (JAVA)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    New Relic -> APM -> Select App (or) Service -> Java -> Installation procedure available.


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
NEW RELIC APM: 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Application Overview: 

    APM -> Click Application 
        Time Picker 
    
        Apdex score 

Service Maps: 

    It shows different connections like front end, application and databases. 

Error Anaytics: 

    APM -> Click Application -> Error , Error Analytics 

Apdex: 

    APDEX - Application Performance Index 

    There is calculation to get apdex score. 

    0 (bad) to 1 (good)


Transactions:    

    Specific transaction can be monitored. 
    Key transaction - Used to monitor the business critical and gives finer details.

Database Monitoring: 
    
    Shows database performance details like throughout, highest execution time etc. 
    


